\pard\f0\fs28   {\b 5. D. moldavica} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 595 (1753). Annual; stems up to 60 cm, erect, glabrous or sparsely hairy. Leaves 15-70 × 7-20 mm, oblong to lanceolate, serrate-crenate, obtuse, glabrous or subglabrous; lower leaves shortly petiolate. Verticillasters 6(-10)-flowered, in the axils of upper leaves, lax below, dense above. Bracts leaf-like. Corolla 20-25 mm, white or violet. Anthers glabrous. {\i Naturalized as a weed and ruderal in E. & E. C. Europe; an occasional, casual elsewhere.} [Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, E).] ({\i Siberia and C. Asia}.)
